laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is hyperemic, dilated (measuring up to 9 mm in maximal diameter), and demonstrates adjacent stranding, all consistent with acute appendicitis. There is no periappendiceal collection or free air. The liver demonstrates no focal lesion. The gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and bilateral kidneys appear unremarkable. Small and large bowel loops are normal in caliber. No mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy is noted.
